{"tid":647784,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"[神秘撚召喚]NASA突然宣佈終止10年探月計劃 科學界震驚","createTime":"2018-04-30T06:40:43.000Z","updateTime":"2018-05-01T12:51:05.000Z","uid":48083,"like":44,"dislike":2,"uniUserReply":64,"replies":[{"pid":"284661dd8a2db82ccd2d2594356e7dbe3de1daeb","tid":647784,"uid":48083,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-04-30T06:40:43.000Z","msg":"中新網4月29日電 據外媒報導，自1972年美國阿波羅17號宇宙飛船成功登月后，探月計劃一直停滯不前。美國總統特朗普曾矢言要再次將美國人送上月球，並下令美國太空總署(NASA)展開探月計劃，但NASA近日宣佈取消研發近10年的&ldquo;資源勘探者&rdquo;(RP)月球探測車任務，令科學界大為震驚。<br />\n<br />\n　　月球探索分析小組(LEAG)上周在網上發布致NASA署長布裏斯坦的信件，表示得悉RP任務於本月23日已被取消，並於下月底正式結束項目，LEAG對此感到沮喪及難以置信。<br />\n<br />\nRP是目前唯一研發中、用作探索月球表面的機械探測車，原定計劃於2022年升空，執行探索月球極地的任務，尋找氫氣、氧氣及水分等生物生存的必要元素。<br />\n<br />\n美國宇航局發布的月球勘測軌道飛行器近期拍攝的圖片，從宇宙飛船角度看，地球似乎正在從月球水平線上&ldquo;升起&rdquo;。<br />\n<br />\n　　NASA其后發聲明響應，強調RP部分儀器將轉移至未來的探月計劃，署方的策略將符合擴大探月任務的目標。<br />\n<br />\n　　不過，俄羅斯航天政策研究所所長伊萬&bull;莫伊塞耶夫表示，美國宇航局(NASA)放棄月球車項目(Resource Prospector)的原因是項目太臃腫。而且美國已經收集了足夠信息，能夠保障衛星順利在月球表面着陸。<br />\n<br />\n　　莫伊塞耶夫说：&ldquo;根據特朗普的命令，載人飛行前往月球，未來將前往火星&rdquo;。這種情況下，RP月球車這種自動化儀器成為多余的項目，因為關於月球的信息已經非常充足，完全可以保障順利着陸&rdquo;。<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"http://dailynews.sina.com/bg/news/int/chinanews/20180428/18348311531.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Fdailynews.sina.com%2Fbg%2Fnews%2Fint%2Fchinanews%2F20180428%2F18348311531.html&d=5wdAhS6aiS079A4rpdC8oQhMEkA7P3Wv%2FuCJwdwWxT4%3D&h=4e84c631\" target=\"_blank\">http://dailynews.sina.com/bg/news/int/chinanews/20180428/18348311531.html</a>"},{"pid":"e61fec4211abb43b09536cae9ba80c016397994f","tid":647784,"uid":48083,"like":5,"dislike":1,"score":4,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-04-30T06:41:52.000Z","msg":"Scientists shocked as NASA cuts only moon rover<br />\n<br />\nIn a move that shocked lunar scientists, NASA has cancelled the only robotic vehicle under development to explore the surface of the Moon, despite President Donald Trump's vow to return people there.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nScientists working on the Resource Prospector (RP) mission, a robotic rover that had been in development for about a decade to explore a polar region of the Moon, expressed astonishment at the decision.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;We now understand RP was cancelled on 23 April 2018 and the project has been asked to close down by the end of May,&quot; said the letter dated April 26 by the Lunar Exploration Analysis Group, addressed to NASA chief Jim Bridenstine and posted on the website <a href=\"http://NASAWatch.com\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2FNASAWatch.com&d=5wdAhS6aiS079A4rpdC8oQhMEkA7P3Wv%2FuCJwdwWxT4%3D&h=9a4534e9\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">NASAWatch.com</a>.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;This action is viewed with both incredulity and dismay by our community,&quot; particularly because Trump's space policy &quot;directs NASA to go to the lunar surface,&quot; the letter said.<br />\n<br />\nThe robotic rover was being built as the world's only vehicle aimed at exploring the polar region of the Moon, and was expected to undergo a design review next year ahead of launching in 2022.<br />\n<br />\nIt would have been the first US lunar lander since Apollo 17 in 1972, and the first ever US robotic rover on the surface of the Moon.<br />\n<br />\nRP was intended to be the first mission to mine the surface of the Moon, in search of volatile compounds like hydrogen, oxygen and water.<br />\n<br />\nNASA responded with a statement posted online Friday which said some of the instruments aboard RP would be flown on future missions.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;NASA is developing an exploration strategy to meet the agency's expanded lunar exploration goals,&quot; said the statement.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;Consistent with this strategy, NASA is planning a series of progressive robotic missions to the lunar surface.&quot;<br />\n<br />\nIt did not specifically refer to any plans to cancel RP, but said the space agency is seeking &quot;to evolve progressively larger landers leading to an eventual human lander capability,&quot; as part of a broader strategy to return people to the Moon for long-term exploration.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;As part of this expanded campaign, selected instruments from Resource Prospector will be landed and flown on the Moon,&quot; it said.<br />\n<br />\nBridenstine, who was confirmed this week as the new head of NASA, insisted on Twitter that the US space agency is &quot;committed to lunar exploration.&quot;<br />\n<br />\n&quot;Resource Prospector instruments will go forward in an expanded lunar surface campaign. More landers. More science. More exploration. More prospectors. More commercial partners,&quot; he wrote.<br />\n<br />\nIn December 2017, Trump formally directed NASA to focus its efforts on returning people to the Moon as a foundation for an eventual mission to Mars.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://phys.org/news/2018-04-scientists-nasa-moon-rover.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fphys.org%2Fnews%2F2018-04-scientists-nasa-moon-rover.html&d=5wdAhS6aiS079A4rpdC8oQhMEkA7P3Wv%2FuCJwdwWxT4%3D&h=449df2e9\" target=\"_blank\">https://phys.org/news/2018-04-scientists-nasa-moon-rover.html</a>"},{"pid":"8bd88a39df1e59709a5b5c12ac232167b69b8ad8","tid":647784,"uid":33868,"like":76,"dislike":2,"score":74,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-04-30T06:42:13.000Z","msg":"嬴國又嬴"},{"pid":"47915957c38a5f90d676c6e8689d21b59dd485ae","tid":647784,"uid":6869,"like":142,"dislike":9,"score":133,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-04-30T06:45:11.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},{"pid":"5b58576962f43f9b4fde90ba9f2a9986bacec1f5","tid":647784,"uid":15812,"like":122,"dislike":4,"score":118,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-04-30T06:46:03.000Z","msg":"會唔會係月球背面有變形金剛所以唔想比人知<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/donno.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"0df2c0623674949a06026b93c14e6593505d3444","tid":647784,"uid":67468,"like":0,"dislike":4,"score":-4,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-04-30T06:46:23.000Z","msg":"悶"},{"pid":"bfda49230dba1c6b0f30964d3